## Iron Loop (15 Steps)

Every feature follows 15 steps. This is non-negotiable. Full details in [IRON_LOOP.md](./IRON_LOOP.md).

```
Phase 1: FUNCTIONAL PLANNING (Steps 1-3)     [Product Owner]
  ASSESS -> ALIGN -> CAPTURE
  Human Gate 1: User approves functional plan

Phase 2: IMPLEMENTATION PLANNING (Steps 4-6)  [Technical]
  PLAN -> DESIGN -> SPEC
  Human Gate 2: User approves technical approach

Phase 3: IMPLEMENTATION (Steps 7-15)          [Autonomous]
  TEST -> PREPARE -> IMPLEMENT -> REVIEW -> OPTIMIZE -> SECURE -> VERIFY -> DOCUMENT -> FINAL-REVIEW
  Human Gate 3: User approves commit/push
```

**Step 7 is TDD** -- write tests FIRST, not "identify coverage".
**Step 9 is ONE step** -- multiple files are sub-items, not separate IMPLEMENT steps.
**Step 13 VERIFY is the quality gate** -- lint, typecheck, ALL tests, coverage >= 80%, 0 skipped, 0 flaky.

### Escape Hatches

User can bypass planning for trivial changes by saying: "skip planning", "quick fix", "trivial fix", "hotfix", "urgent".

